This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with improving retrieval effectiveness through data fusion. It may also belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category as it involves processing and analyzing text data. Additionally, it could be categorized under Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) as it involves combining results from multiple sources. The use of probabilities and machine learning techniques suggests that it could also be classified under Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Databases (cs.DB) sub-categories.
